The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Globe arrest
                                                                                                               Globe arrest
                            
	Behrampore, Jan. 16: A shop owner in Murshidabad has been held for selling a cricket ball-sized globe that showed Kashmir as a separate country.         
	Geography teacher Subir Ghosh bought the made-in-China product from a shop on the way to Hazarduari Palace and took it to police. Ranjan Biswas, the shop owner, and Suraj Dey, his supplier, were held.                                                                                                                                                                              
